'''溫室氣體觀測衛星'''，在[[日本|日本]]又稱為'''氣息號'''<ref>{{cite pressrelease |url=http://www.jaxa.jp/press/2008/10/20081015_gosat_e.html |title='IBUKI' Chosen as Nickname of the Greenhouse Gases Observing Satellite (GOSAT) |publisher=JAXA |date=October 15, 2008 |accessdate=2009-05-29 |archive-date=2008-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222224653/http://www.jaxa.jp/press/2008/10/20081015_gosat_e.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、'''元氣號'''<ref name=Reuters/>，屬於[[地球觀測衛星|地球觀測衛星]]，也是第一枚與監測[[溫室氣體|溫室氣體]]相關的[[人造衛星|人造衛星]]<ref name=AP>{{cite news | title = Japan launches rocket with greenhouse-gas probe | url = http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i8SEG81tZR548fDRwrx_hTHF4z-wD95SU4CO0 | publisher = [[The_Associated_Press|The Associated Press]] | date = Jan 23, 2009 | accessdate = Jan 23, 2009 | archive-date = 2009-01-31 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090131180621/http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i8SEG81tZR548fDRwrx_hTHF4z-wD95SU4CO0 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。主要任務是測量[[大氣層|大氣層]]中的[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]、[[甲烷|甲烷]]之濃度，測量地區多達56,000個<ref name=Reuters>{{cite news | title = Japan launches satellite to monitor greenhouse gases | url = http://www.reuters.com/article/rbssIndustryMaterialsUtilitiesNews/idUST44020090123 | publisher = [[Reuters|Reuters]] | date = Jan 23, 2009 | accessdate = Jan 23, 2009 | first = Chisa | last = Fujioka | archive-date = 2009-02-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090228140724/http://www.reuters.com/article/rbssIndustryMaterialsUtilitiesNews/idUST44020090123 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。溫室氣體觀測衛星由宇宙航空研究開發機構負責製作，並於2009年1月23日從種子島宇宙中心成功發射<ref name=Reuters/>。日本[[环境省|环境省]]與日本[[国立環境研究所|国立環境研究所]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nies.go.jp/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-11-02 |archive-date=2016-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105061047/http://www.nies.go.jp/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>藉由這顆人造衛星來了解溫室效應對於環境的影響並與[[美国国家航空航天局|美国国家航空航天局]]共享資料，以獲得近一步的突破<ref name=AP/>。

== 發射 ==
溫室氣體觀測衛星與其他七顆人造衛星一同由[[H-IIA运载火箭|H-IIA运载火箭]]在2009年1月23日從種子島宇宙中心升空，由於天候不佳的因素，中途曾經推遲2天的發射時程<ref name=Reuters/><ref name=AP/>，大約經過16分鐘的火箭飛行後，溫室氣體觀測衛星與火箭本體成功分離<ref name=JAXA>{{cite web | title = Greenhouse gases Observing SATellite "IBUKI"(GOSAT) | url = http://www.jaxa.jp/projects/sat/gosat/index_e.html | publisher = [[Japan_Aerospace_Exploration_Agency|Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency]] | accessdate = Jan 23, 2009 | archive-date = 2014-04-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140404152255/http://www.jaxa.jp/projects/sat/gosat/index_e.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>，最終也成功進入觀測軌道。
== 儀器 ==
根據宇宙航空研究開發機構的資訊，溫室氣體觀測衛星具備紅外傅立葉變換光譜儀、熱和近紅外傳感器兩項主要科學儀器，觀測波長從紅外線到遠紅外線區均有<ref name=JAXA/>，主要觀測原理則是藉由[[光譜儀|光譜儀]]來測量與分辨不同的物質，因為不同的物質具有布一樣的光折射率，也可以得知不同溫室氣體的濃度<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.calgaryherald.com/Technology/Alta+scientists+monitor+oilsands+from+space/1203112/story.html | first = Keith | last = Gerein | title = Alta. scientists to track greenhouse gases from space | publisher = Calgary Herald | date = January 21, 2009 | accessdate = January 24, 2009 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090131213032/http://www.calgaryherald.com/Technology/Alta+scientists+monitor+oilsands+from+space/1203112/story.html | archivedate = 2009年1月31日 }}</ref>。
